        <div id="dsq-comment-body-29" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-29" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>At 51% hashing power, he gains the option to do this.</p>
</div>
        </div>

    <ul class="children">
    <li class="comment odd alt depth-4" id="dsq-comment-36">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-36" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-36">
http://twitter.com/JoelKatz                <span id="dsq-author-user-36">David Schwartz</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-36" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-36" class="dsq-comment-message"><p> He doesn&#8217;t just gain the option, but he gains the incentive. Say he has 60% of the mining power. If he mines &#8220;honestly&#8221;, he mines 60% of the blocks and gets 60% of the rewards. If he only builds off his own blocks, he gets 100% of the block rewards. Since the block rewards are fixed for now at 50 bitcoins per 10 minutes, he has a strong incentive to only build off his own blocks.</p>
<p>However, he has no incentive (unless his motive is to kill Bitcoins) not to include transactions. If he includes no transactions, he makes Bitcoins useless and reduces the value of the Bitcoins he has mined.</p>
</div>
        </div>

    <ul class="children">
    <li class="comment even depth-5" id="dsq-comment-53">
