            <div id="dsq-comment-message-31" class="dsq-comment-message"><p> Ah yes, now I see what you were referring to.  Didn&#8217;t even think of this attack (but who would do this kind of DoS if he could actually make money by spending his bitcoins twice?! <img src="https://www.privateinternetaccess.com/blog/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" /> </p>
<p>Other than that, you write about the transactions fees that this host doesn&#8217;t collect. Transaction fees currently are at about 0.02 BTC per block (for the blocks I checked), so he doesn&#8217;t really loose much.  If people payed more fees, maybe that host would start to behave more socially?</p>
</div>
        </div>

